1.  Whom God causes to perish, He always first makes him inflated;
2.  Time is a sieve, ultimately it will sift out all dregs;
3.  Bees steal from flowers, yet the result causes the flowers to bloom luxuriantly;
4.  When it's utterly dark, one can see the starlight even more.
